sentences: Albert Dupuis (1 March 1877 – 19 September 1967) was a Belgian composer.
Albert Dupuis was born in Verviers on 1 March 1877.
Noticed by the French composer and teacher Vincent d'Indy in 1897, Dupuis was invited to work with him at the Schola Cantorum in Paris.
He was for a time the coach of the choir of Saint-Eustache, but in 1900 he returned to Verviers to marry.

In 1903 he won the Prix de Rome Belgium (not to be confused with the French Prix de Rome) with his cantata La Chanson d'Halewyn and on 5 March his opera Jean-Michel premiered at La Monnaie, the Royal Theatre of the Mint in Brussels..

In 1903 he won the Prix de Rome Belgium (not to be confused with the French Prix de Rome) with his cantata La Chanson d'Halewyn and on 5 March his opera Jean-Michel premiered at La Monnaie, the Royal Theatre of the Mint in Brussels..
Appointed conductor of the Theatre of Ghent in 1905, he withdrew when the season was completed, to devote himself to composition.
But when in 1907 the council of Verviers offered him the post of director at the conservatory, he accepted and held it until his retirement in 1947.
